You can use the following JavaScript code in the Chrome Developer Console to get a copy of the entire page HTML:

```javascript
let html = document.documentElement.outerHTML;
console.log(html);
copy(html);
```

This code will first store the entire HTML of the page in the `html` variable, then log it in the console, and finally copy it to your clipboard. Please note that the `copy()` function may not work in some browsers due to security restrictions. In that case, you can manually copy the logged HTML from the console.

To access the Chrome Developer Console, you can use the shortcut `Ctrl + Shift + J` on Windows/Linux or `Cmd + Option + J` on macOS, or right-click on the webpage and select "Inspect" and then click on the "Console" tab.

